58","id":18746903,"user":{"login":"florinpeter","id":2911849,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/df9570ff71909a99f01eb4307bce8bf8?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fd503a45d4a0b5139f9c7bb65e4786414.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"df9570ff71909a99f01eb4307bce8bf8","url":"https://api.github.com/users/florinpeter","html_url":"https://github.com/florinpeter","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/florinpeter/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/florinpeter/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/florinpeter/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/florinpeter/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/florinpeter/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/florinpeter/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/florinpeter/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/florinpeter/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/florinpeter/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-05-31t14:08:35z","updated_at":"2013-05-31t14:08:35z","body":"@blizzz your right blocking the user from login was a bad idea. i changed this now so only file actions from the encryption app are disabled."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18831865","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/3558#issuecomment-18831865","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3558","id":18831865,"user":{"login":"schiesbn","id":1589737,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/8912b598c7b32dd25b87fd168e0b06b2?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f0a323047dbe8329db30eae8dbe96e55e.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"8912b598c7b32dd25b87fd168e0b06b2","url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn","html_url":"https://github.com/schiesbn","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-06-03t10:01:21z","updated_at":"2013-06-03t10:01:21z","body":"the admin can only handle the situation if the recovery key was enabled and also in this case probably only if the backend allows the admin to change the login password through onwcloud.  currently we use the owncloud user management to recover the files during password change.  @blizzz can you check this with a ldap server. i fear that password recovery will not work at all in such a environment.\r\n\r\ni don't know what's the best solution here? still let the admin set passwords in the user management but somehow make clear that in this case only the keys will changed?\r\n\r\ngenerally, if the password was changed in the auth back-end i would expect that the user still knows his old password. so we should provide a dialogue or a option in the personal settings which allows him to change his key password by providing the old and the new password. "},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18833060","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/3558#issuecomment-18833060","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3558","id":18833060,"user":{"login":"blizzz","id":2184312,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/1898b25a9cb3aa1a0f0febd1359910b9?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fca03acec6deadf508b75eb0cf9ba036c.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"1898b25a9cb3aa1a0f0febd1359910b9","url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz","html_url":"https://github.com/blizzz","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-06-03t10:33:07z","updated_at":"2013-06-03t10:33:07z","body":"@schiesbn password change is not handled via owncloud using ldap backend. this is why we opened #3555 you find you suggestion there as well, though less detailed ;)"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18837728","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/3558#issuecomment-18837728","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3558","id":18837728,"user":{"login":"schiesbn","id":1589737,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/8912b598c7b32dd25b87fd168e0b06b2?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f0a323047dbe8329db30eae8dbe96e55e.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"8912b598c7b32dd25b87fd168e0b06b2","url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn","html_url":"https://github.com/schiesbn","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-06-03t12:30:07z","updated_at":"2013-06-03t12:31:10z","body":"in case the ldap admin changed the password i would just show a option in the personal settings where the user can change his key password from the old log-in password to the new one.\r\n\r\nbut the general recovery function which is handled by ownclouds user management until now might be a bit tricky. i would like to keep it in the user management because i think it fits nicely and integrates well. but how should we present it to the admin if he can only change the key password but not the login password? maybe some ideas by our designers? cc @owncloud/designers"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18838055","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/3558#issuecomment-18838055","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3558","id":18838055,"user":{"login":"blizzz","id":2184312,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/1898b25a9cb3aa1a0f0febd1359910b9?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fca03acec6deadf508b75eb0cf9ba036c.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"1898b25a9cb3aa1a0f0febd1359910b9","url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz","html_url":"https://github.com/blizzz","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-06-03t12:37:05z","updated_at":"2013-06-03t12:37:05z","body":"it's not necessarily the ldap admin, also the ldap user him/her/itself, it does not happen via owncloud either way. so the user needs to be able to readjust his key password in first place (but of course also admin on forgotten passwords). "},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18841271","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/3558#issuecomment-18841271","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3558","id":18841271,"user":{"login":"schiesbn","id":1589737,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/8912b598c7b32dd25b87fd168e0b06b2?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f0a323047dbe8329db30eae8dbe96e55e.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"8912b598c7b32dd25b87fd168e0b06b2","url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn","html_url":"https://github.com/schiesbn","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-06-03t13:34:56z","updated_at":"2013-06-03t13:34:56z","body":"the last commits enabled the user to update his private key password in case the ldap admin changed the log-in password.\r\n\r\n> so the user needs to be able to readjust his key password in first place (but of course also admin on forgotten passwords). \r\n\r\nthat's now possible but still the owncloud admin needs to be able to reset the users encryption key in case of password loss. at the moment this is handled in the owncloud user management, where the encryption key gets reset automatically if the owncloud admin changes the users password. if possible i would keep this, because it is really nice integrated. but we need to somehow tell the owncloud admin that if the user back-end doesn't support password change than the user management password field is only usable to change the users encryption key password."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18907822","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/3558#issuecomment-18907822","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3558","id":18907822,"user":{"login":"schiesbn","id":1589737,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/8912b598c7b32dd25b87fd168e0b06b2?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f0a323047dbe8329db30eae8dbe96e55e.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"8912b598c7b32dd25b87fd168e0b06b2","url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn","html_url":"https://github.com/schiesbn","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-06-04t13:13:16z","updated_at":"2013-06-04t13:13:16z","body":"i think this pull request is ready for review. additionally to the points mentioned in the initial pull request we now also provide the possibility for the user to change his encryption key password once the admin changed his log-in password to regain access to his data. \r\n\r\nwo wants to review it? @blizzz @deepdiver1975 @karlitschek and of course everybody else is welcome to review it!"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18938374","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/3558#issuecomment-18938374","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3558","id":18938374,"user":{"login":"blizzz","id":2184312,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/1898b25a9cb3aa1a0f0febd1359910b9?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fca03acec6deadf508b75eb0cf9ba036c.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"1898b25a9cb3aa1a0f0febd1359910b9","url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz","html_url":"https://github.com/blizzz","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-06-04t20:54:06z","updated_at":"2013-06-04t20:54:06z","body":"i will give it a try tomorrow."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18969999","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/3558#issuecomment-18969999","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3558","id":18969999,"user":{"login":"blizzz","id":2184312,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/1898b25a9cb3aa1a0f0febd1359910b9?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fca03acec6deadf508b75eb0cf9ba036c.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"1898b25a9cb3aa1a0f0febd1359910b9","url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz","html_url":"https://github.com/blizzz","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-06-05t11:34:25z","updated_at":"2013-06-05t11:34:25z","body":"everything works!  just three things where they may be improvements. besides this, already a :+1: \r\n\r\n1) after logging in with new password and clicking on an encrypted text file, the message appears:\r\n\r\n> your private key is not valid! maybe your password was changed from outside.\r\n\r\nwould be great to give a hint how/where to fix this. like \"please go to personal settings and update the private key password\"\r\n\r\n2) on the personal page the section \"encryption\" exists with just some white space. leave it out totally, when everything is fine.\r\n(wait, shouldn't there be an option to enable recovery?)\r\n\r\n3) give a hint what to do when you forgot your old password on the personal page."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18971042","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/3558#issuecomment-18971042","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3558","id":18971042,"user":{"login":"schiesbn","id":1589737,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/8912b598c7b32dd25b87fd168e0b06b2?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f0a323047dbe8329db30eae8dbe96e55e.png&r=x","gr